-- Indonesia mandates banks for up to $1.5 bln sovereign sukuk
-- By Mirna Sleiman
-- Mon May 26, 2014 05:10AM EDT
-- None



DUBAI, May 26 (Reuters) - Indonesia has mandated HSBC <HSBA.L>, Standard Chartered <STAN.L> and CIMB Group Holdings Bhd <CIMB.KL> to arrange a sovereign sukuk issue of up to $1.5 billion, sources aware of the matter told Reuters on Monday.

